            <div class="answer">
                
                    <span>Mikerhys, I&#39;m sorry but I think that you misunderstood what Narayanan Sri was asking.  He was noting that the 500k borrowed from the bank and backed by the home equity was not destroyed, it was merely transferred from the bank to the home owner and finally to the vendors that refurbished the home.  Note also that the calculation that you wrote out assumes that the home owners paid off their mortgages and actually lost 250K of equity.  In Sal&#39;s example that was not the case.</span>
                
            </div>

